   Executive MBA Event

Paris | Sep 21, 2019

   Executive MBA Event

     * Print
     * Star

     * Envelope
     * Share
          +
          +
          +
          +
          +

     * Why Attend Features
     * Time & Place Time & Place
     * What is an EMBA EMBA
     * How to Book Meetings FAQ

   This boutique high-profile Executive MBA (EMBA) event features:
     * A unique VIP service for business executives to boost their career
       with EMBA studies
     * Private meetings with top EMBA Directors upon invitation only
     * Personalised consulting on career development and the value of EMBA
     * Individual orientation on the features of international top EMBA
       programmes
     * Networking with executives aspiring to senior business leadership
     * EMBA funding portfolio and ROI analysis
     * Free access to MBA One-to-One meetings at the accompanying Access
       MBA event

   Access EMBA equips business executives with insights from leading
   global EMBA programmes.
   Schedule
   Saturday, September 21, 2019
   9:30 AM:
   Welcome Desk opens
   10:00 AM – 3:30 PM:
   One-to-One meetings
   * Requires CV or LinkedIn profile upload
   Venue
   Le Méridien Etoile
   Address: 81, Bd Gouvion St Cyr
   Metro Station: Porte Maillot
   Le Méridien Etoile Le Méridien Etoile
   View large map

   Executive MBA (EMBA) programmes are designed for professionals with
   over six years of work experience who target top management careers and
   senior business leadership roles.

   Joining an EMBA programme enables executives to advance their
   successful career while they add the value of MBA degree studies and
   networking.

   Delivered in part-time, executive or modular formats EMBA programmes
   are designed to accommodate the busy schedules of high-level managers.

   Participants in EMBA gain further advantage of the unique opportunity
   to impact company growth and transformation by implementing newly
   developed skills and knowledge immediately.

   Make the most of a personalised executive orientation service

   The One-to-One Executive MBA meetings are held upon invitation only,
   reflecting the goals and preferences of business executives as well as
   how well their profiles meet the requirements of leading EMBA
   programmes, including:
     * A Bachelor’s degree (or the equivalent) or a higher degree
     * Fluent English for academic studies and communication
     * Over 6 years of relevant work experience after graduation including
       3 years of managerial experience
     __________________________________________________________________

   Step 1: Complete the online profile and registration form to enable
   Access EMBA orientation experts to review your academic and
   professional profile and MBA preferences.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Step 2: Be available to Access EMBA orientation experts, in case they
   need to contact you by phone or email to ensure thorough understanding
   of your individual EMBA project, motivation, and aspirations.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Step 3: After you submit the registration, Access EMBA orientation
   experts identify the best matching programmes to ensure your
   eligibility for admission and fit for your goals and profile.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Step 4: Review the Access EMBA invitation that describes how you can
   benefit from the event – One-to-One meetings, onsite orientation or
   admissions consulting, etc. Once you receive the list and details about
   the best-matching EMBA programmes for your personal meetings, you can
   discuss and amend it with a dedicated consultant.
   Media partners

   Manhattan Review - France

